closeOnEscape.description: Whether to close the drawer when the escape key is pressed.

closeOnInteractOutside.description: Whether to close the drawer when the outside is clicked.

closeThreshold.description: The threshold distance for dismissing the drawer.

defaultOpen.description: The initial open state of the drawer.

finalFocusEl.description: Element to receive focus when the sheet is closed.

id.description: The unique identifier of the machine.

ids.description: The ids of the elements in the drawer. Useful for composition.

immediate.description: Whether to synchronize the present change immediately or defer it to the next frame

initialFocusEl.description: Element to receive focus when the sheet is opened.

modal.description: Whether to prevent pointer interaction outside the element and hide all content below it.

onEscapeKeyDown.description: Function called when the escape key is pressed

onExitComplete.description: Function called when the animation ends in the closed state

onFocusOutside.description: Function called when the focus is moved outside the component

onInteractOutside.description: Function called when an interaction happens outside the component

onOpenChange.description: Function called when the open state changes.

onPointerDownOutside.description: Function called when the pointer is pressed down outside the component

onRequestDismiss.description: Function called when this layer is closed due to a parent layer being closed

onSnapPointChange.description: Callback fired when the snap point changes.

present.description: Whether the node is present (controlled by the user)

preventDragOnScroll.description:
Whether to prevent dragging on scrollable elements.
When enabled, the sheet will not start dragging if the user is interacting with a scrollable element.

preventScroll.description: Whether to prevent scrolling behind the sheet when it's opened

restoreFocus.description: Whether to restore focus to the element that had focus before the sheet was opened.

skipAnimationOnMount.description: Whether to allow the initial presence animation.

snapPoints.description:
The snap points of the drawer.
Array of numbers or strings representing the snap points.

snapToSequentialPoints.description: Whether the drawer should snap to sequential points when swiping.

stack.description:
Optional external store for coordinating app-level drawer stack visuals
(e.g. indent and background layers).

swipeDirection.description: The direction in which the drawer can be swiped.

swipeVelocityThreshold.description: The threshold velocity (in pixels/s) for closing the drawer.

trapFocus.description: Whether to trap focus inside the sheet when it's opened.
